        "timestamp": "2018-06-29 10:52:06.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nHi Pam, I ran Jacoco/Sonar build locally and integration tests are showing up in code coverage. \n\nmvn clean install -e -Dsonar --settings /home/Waqas/Desktop/onap_settings.xml\n\nfor example\nElement\tCoverage\tCovered Instructions\tMissed Instructions\tTotal Instructions\nplugins-event-carrier-restclient\t79.5 %\t494\t127\t621\nplugins-event-carrier-websocket\t66.0 %\t280\t144\t424\nintegration-uservice-test\t63.1 %\t5,114\t2,994\t8,108\nplugins-event-carrier-restserver\t60.9 %\t510\t327\t837\nplugins-event-carrier-kafka\t57.9 %\t561\t408\t969\nplugins-event-protocol-jms\t52.5 %\t166\t150\t316\ncore-engine\t50.5 %\t2,742\t2,689\t5,431\nplugins-executor-mvel\t47.6 %\t212\t233\t445\n\n\nPer my knowledge of jacoco/sonar these test should not be ignored as these integration tests are Junit test.\n\nWill investigate further if otherwise.\n\nAnd, These are not CSIT tests.\n\nRegards,\nWaqas",
        "patchset_number": 5
